com.ibm.team.repository.common.query

Interface IDataQueryPage

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IQueryPage

    public interface IDataQueryPage
extends IQueryPage

    Represents the definition of a query page for data queries. Results from a data query can be thought of as a two-dimensional array of returned data values. The first dimension represents a tuple comprising the fields or computed values specified in the projection clause of a query. The second dimension represents multiple occurrences of the tuple, or rows of data.

    Clients will generally process a data query page by iterating through each of the data rows. For each data row, clients can access the data values using either index-based or name-based lookup.

    Data query results are self describing; each field in a row is assigned a name and knows its type. Clients can use this for introspecting the shape of the query result and retrieving values from the data rows.

    Since:
    0.5
    See Also:
    IQueryPage, IDataRow, IDataField

    • Method Detail

      • getRow

        IDataRow getRow(int position)
        Answers the row of result data at the 0-based position, relative to the size of this page.
        Parameters:
        position - non-negative zero-based index of the request row; must be less than the size of this page
        Returns:
        an IDataRow containing row data for the given position; never null
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index >= size()).

      • getDataFields

        java.util.List getDataFields()
        Answers the list of field descriptions that compose a row of data. The size will match the number of fields in each row, which will match the number of elements in the projection clause of the query.
        Returns:
        List of IDataField - will never be null or empty
